## II. Content Architecture Principles

### Visual Hierarchy System (Nested Prompt Model)

Map nested prompt hierarchy to slide structure for optimal information architecture:

**Level 1: Presentation (System)**
- Overall theme and central message
- Duration: 30-90 seconds total
- Slide count: 3-7 slides maximum
- Purpose: Complete narrative arc with clear beginning, middle, end

**Level 2: Section (Agent/Project)**
- Major topic blocks within presentation
- Structure: 1 title slide + 2-4 content slides per section
- Flow: Clear narrative progression
- Transitions: Smooth topic shifts with contextual bridges

**Level 3: Slide (User)**
- Single concept per slide (one idea only)
- Components: 1 heading + 3-5 bullets maximum
- Duration: 10-15 seconds speaking time per slide
- Rule: Never exceed 20 seconds per slide

**Level 4: Element (Sub-prompt)**
- Individual bullet points or text fragments
- Length: 5-10 words maximum per bullet
- Format: Sentence fragments, not complete sentences
- Visual: Icons preferred over dense text when applicable

### Workshop/Training Presentation Style

**Tone Guidelines:**
- **Professional yet conversational** - Expert but accessible
- **Thought leadership positioning** - Authoritative without arrogance
- **Warm, not corporate-cold** - Human, approachable, empathetic
- **Inclusive pronouns** - Use "we" and "you" (je in Dutch)
- **Question-driven engagement** - Prompt audience reflection

**Pacing Rules:**
- Title slides: 3-4 seconds (quick impact, introduce topic)
- Content slides: 10-15 seconds (digestible information chunks)
- Image slides: 5-8 seconds (visual emphasis without explanation)
- **Never exceed 20 seconds per slide** (pace slows, attention wanes)

**Language Patterns:**
- Questions engage audience: "Wat wil je leren?" "How can we improve?"
- Frameworks use acronyms: CRAFT, CODE, PARA
- Bullets use action-oriented verbs: "Build", "Create", "Learn"
- Avoid jargon: Use simple Dutch/English, explain technical terms
- Hashtags for branding: [#YourHashtag], #ai, #productiviteit

